{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QKsx1nTTD8D86C81TUwqa4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a critical bug! The SQL query uses `ARRAY JOIN arrayJoin(...)` which is incorrect syntax. The issue is that you can't use `ARRAY JOIN` with `arrayJoin()` function — these are different things. \n\nThe `ARRAY JOIN` clause in ClickHouse works with column expressions of array type, but `arrayJoin()` is a table function that already expands the array into rows. They shouldn't be combined. The correct approach would be to use either:\n- `ARRAY JOIN JSONExtractKeys(properties)` (using `ARRAY JOIN` clause alone)\n\n\n- Or `arrayJoin(JSONExtractKeys(properties))` in the SELECT clause without `ARRAY JOIN`\n\nThe error confirms this: when ClickHouse processes `ARRAY JOIN arrayJoin(...)`, it executes `arrayJoin()` first which produces strings, then tries to apply `ARRAY JOIN` to those strings which requires Array or Map type. I need to pick one approach — either the `ARRAY JOIN` clause or the `arrayJoin()` function, but not both.\n\nThis is actually a real bug that the HTTP integration check caught, since the unit tests mock the ClickHouse client entirely. Let me test the corrected SQL directly against ClickHouse to confirm it works.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":794,"cache_read_input_tokens":51631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":794},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bf5c5d54-f5be-4f7e-81c9-7cee309979d4","uuid":"7cd4ed06-03ce-4de0-814e-175c19de6526"}
